Guy Belleau has been appointed COO of ArcelorMittal Mining Canada, a subsidiary of steel giant ArcelorMittal that operates on Quebec’s North Shore. "I am pleased to welcome Guy within our renewed management team. Our goal is to become a world reference in the safe and efficient production of iron-ore by 2024 and having Guy on our team is a major asset to help us reach this goal,” comments recently appointed CEO Mapi Mobwano. Belleau has more than 30 years of experience in the mining industry. Prior to joining the ArcelorMittal team, he was general manager of the Horne 5 mine of Falco Resources. Previously, he worked with companies such as Goldcorp and Xstrata.